PERTH (miningweekly.com) â€“ Dan Clifford has tendered his resignation as MD of coal miner Stanmore Coal, with the company on Friday announcing the appointment of Jon Romcke as interim CEO. Clifford has been MD of Stanmore for about three years, having joined the company shortly after the restart of the Isaac Plains mine. Stanmore told shareholders that a recruitment process would start immediately to replace Clifford, who would remain in the business until late November to work with Romcke and the leadership team in order to manage the handover. Romcke, who is the GM of development at Stanmore, has previously held the role of MD at Sphere Minerals and has worked for Xstrata Iron Ore in Switzerland and at Xstrata Coal in Queensland.